The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
		 Monday, May 19, 2003 				 63 doctors rapped in past three years
		 Medical Council members  sift through the relevant documents attached to a formal  complaint against a doctor. Pictures by Kishor Roy ChowdhuryAnil Mukherjee: So many complaints are lodged against doctors. Can you tell us how many of them have been punished in recent years?																																																													During the period 2000-2003, the West Bengal Medical Council recorded 98 cases against doctors. Of them, 35 could not be substantiated. Action was taken in the rest of the cases. The doctors were either warned or censured. Some were suspended for six months to a year.
